$ SQLite: drop table
@ drop table

{ Dropping a table only if it exists #drop-table-if-exists

  In order to suppress error messages, → development/databases/SQLite supports the `drop table if exists` clause which only tries to drop a → development/databases/SQLite/tables/[table] if it in fact *does* exist:
  gh|about-sqlite|/tables/drop_if_exists.sql||

  See also → development/databases/SQLite/views/drop#drop-view-if-exists


}

sa:
  → development/databases/SQLite/tables

  → development/databases/SQLite/tables/create
